output.crosstab_text:
Among those who graduated five years previously from first degree courses in Psychology and who were working during the 2021-22 tax year, Human health and social work activities was the most common industry for those living in the North East, the North West, Yorkshire and The Humber, the East Midlands, the East of England, London, the South East and the South West, and Education and Human health and social work activities were the most common industries for those living in the West Midlands.

The group with the highest earnings was graduates living in London who worked in the Information and communication industry (median earnings of £45,300).
